.SH NAME
images \- Interactive menu launcher for image viewing applications
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B images
[\fI\,IMAGE_FILE\fR] [\fI\,OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B images
is an interactive menu-driven launcher for image viewing and editing applications that provides a terminal-based interface with zenity/dialog file selection integration. It offers one-click access to multiple image viewers with automatic installation support for missing applications, file/folder selection dialogs, and persistent menu system with configurable countdown.
.PP
The script simplifies image application launching by providing interactive terminal menu with visual prompts, multiple image viewer support (sxiv, gimp, shotwell, etc.), automatic package installation via pkmgr integration, zenity file selection dialogs for GUI environments, dialog fallback for terminal-only systems, custom application launcher with file chooser, and countdown timer with auto-menu reload.
.PP
images is particularly useful for unified image viewer access point, quick switching between image applications, headless server remote GUI application launching, desktop environment-agnostic image viewing, and automated installation of missing image tools.
