.SH MENU BEHAVIOR
How images manages menu lifecycle:
.SS Menu Loop
.RS
.EX
while :; do
  trap '' SIGINT SIGQUIT SIGTSTP
  # Display menu
  # Take action based on choice
  printf_counter "$IMAGES_OUTPUT_COLOR" "$IMAGES_COUNTDOWN_TIME" "Re-loading menu in"
done
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Infinite loop until user selects "z" (Exit)
.IP \(bu 2
Traps SIGINT/SIGQUIT/SIGTSTP to prevent accidental exit
.IP \(bu 2
Countdown timer after each operation
.IP \(bu 2
Auto-reloads menu after countdown
.RE
.SS Countdown Timer
.RS
.EX
printf_counter "$IMAGES_OUTPUT_COLOR" "$IMAGES_COUNTDOWN_TIME" "Re-loading menu in"
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Configurable countdown (default: 3 seconds)
.IP \(bu 2
IMAGES_COUNTDOWN_TIME environment variable
.IP \(bu 2
Visual countdown before menu reload
.IP \(bu 2
User can wait or press key to skip
.RE
